misconceptions.remediation_hint:
Inside the while loop, after printing the 'Too low'/'Too high' hint, prompt the user again and read a new guess, e.g.:

```java
while (guess != answer) {
    if (guess < answer) {
        System.out.println("Too low, try again.");
    } else {
        System.out.println("Too high, try again.");
    }
    System.out.print("Guess my number: ");
    guess = input.nextInt();
}
System.out.println("Correct!");
```

